subSubSection.paragraph:
Male. (Revised after Kimmins in 
Mosely and Kimmins 1953
; 
Neboiss 1977
, 
2003
). Tergum X membranous with a pair of small lobes (
Fig. 33
). Superior appendages laterally compressed; in lateral view robust, sub-rectangular, length about 2.5 times width (
Fig. 31
); in dorsal view, relatively slender, length about 4 times width, with spines on inner surface (
Fig. 33
). Phallus simple, tube-like; with a single, elongate, down-curved sword-like process (phallic guide) arising from near the base of the inferior appendages (
Fig. 31
). Inferior appendages dorso-ventrally flattened, fused to form a single, elongate plate; in ventral view length about 2.0 times width, with a small central notch apically (
Fig. 32
); in lateral view slender, slightly curved, length about 6 times width (
Fig. 31
).

Female. (Revised after 
Neboiss 1977
). Genitalia with a pair of large relatively widely separated ‘tongueshaped’ lobes with pointed apices, on sternite VIII (
Fig. 59
).
